Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.17,0:00:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A racing second hand,\Na shooting comet,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.25,0:00:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a pop-up doll,\Nand broken ceramic!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.00,0:00:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mystery-solving logic is helpful\Nagainst people's dry hearts!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.58,0:00:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's a beautiful illustrator!\NHer mischievous streak means death!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.17,0:00:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth for what it is,\Nand there's no outwitting him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.12,0:00:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.17,0:01:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Illustrator Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.17,0:01:57.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Illustrator Murder Case
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.09,0:02:02.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanaoka Design Office
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.76,0:01:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? A collection of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.89,0:02:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,murder scene paintings?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.05,0:02:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't tell you?\NIt's being released next month
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.23,0:02:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by painter and president of this\Ndesign office, Hanaoka-{\i1}sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.81,0:02:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked both of you to come\Ntoday for an interview
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.78,0:02:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to put at the end\Nof the collection...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.65,0:02:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interview?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.83,0:02:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.49,0:02:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that Dad said it was\Na collection of paintings of him!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.17,0:02:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed strange, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.00,0:02:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.67,0:02:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, where is this fancy painter?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.84,0:02:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's still not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.14,0:02:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He could be asleep in his studio...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.72,0:02:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.26,0:02:47.73,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Beika Apartment Building #2
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.11,0:02:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.82,0:02:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you woke up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.11,0:02:59.70,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Painter - Kenjin Hanaoka (48)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.94,0:02:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this? Paint?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.11,0:03:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nail polish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.11,0:03:04.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Illustrator - Izumi Chono (25)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.03,0:03:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a nice color?\Nlt went on sale today!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.78,0:03:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.20,0:03:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should you really be relaxing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.37,0:03:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you supposed to meet\Nsome detective at 5:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.88,0:03:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.13,0:03:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.46,0:03:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I put your pants\Nand socks on for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't pull that prank anymore!\NIf my wife were to see it-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.76,0:03:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.51,0:03:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way she'd divorce you\Nand we could be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.06,0:03:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you our relationship\Nis business only!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.03,0:03:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you're able\Nto paint whatever you want
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.07,0:03:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and live in such a fancy apartment!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.87,0:03:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll reveal the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.24,0:03:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's already vaguely suspicious.\NBut she overlooks it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.75,0:03:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mean us.\NI mean the paintings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.46,0:04:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sixty percent of your paintings\Nwere actually done by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:04.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If word gets out, you can kiss\Nyour reputation goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.06,0:04:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be able to\Nsell a single painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.23,0:04:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who'd ever believe\Na new illustrator?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.19,0:04:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you didn't know?\NI clearly marked each one I drew.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.32,0:04:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.07,0:04:26.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The World of Kenjin Hanaoka
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.53,0:04:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a good look beneath\Nyour signature on the paintings I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.54,0:04:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.75,0:04:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've placed that mark\Non all of my original works.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.46,0:04:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to your increase in work,\Nthey've become rather famous...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.30,0:04:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I stayed up all night\Npainting another.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.89,0:04:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to have it delivered\Nto the publisher later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.23,0:05:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try as you might,\Nthere's no escape from me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.48,0:05:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...for as long as you live.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.74,0:05:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's late! It's already 5:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.91,0:05:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No luck. He's not at home,\Nand I get his machine at the studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.08,0:05:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Chono-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s place?\NToday was her deadline...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.83,0:05:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chono?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.25,0:05:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A new illustrator.\NShe lives in that building right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.80,0:05:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! I didn't mean to kill her!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.02,0:05:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Chono.\NI'm away at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.35,0:05:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please leave your\Nmessage after the tone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.86,0:05:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello. This is Tanaka\Nfrom Hanaoka Design.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.11,0:05:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chono-{\i1}kun{\i0}. Are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.95,0:05:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanaoka Design!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:05:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.58,0:05:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.38,0:06:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A prank call.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.13,0:06:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking at,\NConan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.67,0:06:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That apartment's veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.80,0:06:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.72,0:06:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They left their mattress\Nout in the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.35,0:06:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah. That's Chono-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.77,0:06:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess she's asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.73,0:06:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is taking far too long!\NSorry, but I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.86,0:06:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.53,0:06:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.99,0:06:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanaoka-{\i1}sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.41,0:06:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.71,0:06:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I fell asleep in my studio...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.00,0:06:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your studio? We called\Nthere several times...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.34,0:06:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's what woke me up...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.76,0:06:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting,\NDetective Mori!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.55,0:06:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What happened\Nto your fingernail?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My fingernail?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:07:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that nail polish?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.10,0:07:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not! It's just paint!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.69,0:07:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Must've gotten it in my studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.28,0:07:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Tanaka-{\i1}kun{\i0}.\NChono-{\i1}kun {\i0}might call.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.36,0:07:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Transfer the call to me if she does.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.03,0:07:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.24,0:07:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! Damn! Damn that woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.50,0:07:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanaoka Design!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.84,0:07:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Chono.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.72,0:07:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's you! Just a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.30,0:07:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir! It's Chono-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.18,0:07:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Hanaoka.\NAre you feeling any better?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.77,0:07:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're going to die?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.23,0:07:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to jump off the veranda?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.33,0:08:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She jumped off!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.75,0:08:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is Izumi Chono,\N25 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.92,0:08:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanaoka-{\i1}san{\i0}. She was an illustrator\Nfor your design firm, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.55,0:08:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She was still new,\Nbut she had a keen sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.31,0:08:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But on the phone she said she was\Ngoing to die since she had no talent...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.90,0:08:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the next thing I knew,\Nshe had jumped off the veranda...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.53,0:08:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you all witnessed it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.74,0:08:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.03,0:08:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A contact lens?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.24,0:08:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. Wasn't she--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.29,0:08:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With so many witnesses,\Nit must've been a suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.88,0:08:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! This was a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.22,0:08:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet she was dead before she fell,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.30,0:08:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that someone pushed her over!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.60,0:09:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In which case,\Nthe most suspicious is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.14,0:09:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...this man, who tried\Nto talk her out of suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.98,0:09:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could an accomplice have pushed her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.65,0:09:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there was no one\Non the veranda when she fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.74,0:09:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how did he push her\Noff from so far away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.04,0:09:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, isn't this strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.67,0:09:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at her eyes.\NShe's wearing contacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.92,0:09:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.51,0:09:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she was wearing\Nglasses when she fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.18,0:09:41.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who wears glasses when\Nthey already have contacts in?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.81,0:09:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has a point...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.18,0:09:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, someone put her\Nglasses on before pushing her off?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.36,0:09:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.98,0:09:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective. You saw\Nher jump off for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.65,0:10:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was nobody else\Non the veranda at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.66,0:10:01.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Chono
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.54,0:10:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? The door's unlocked...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.80,0:10:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A nail...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.51,0:10:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's it doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.55,0:10:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.43,0:10:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! Watch this kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.72,0:10:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the veranda\Nshe jumped off of...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.14,0:10:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Slippers, a cell phone,\Nand a broken flowerpot...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.94,0:10:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The flowerpot pieces\Nlead to the drain...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.95,0:10:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know you shouldn't\Nsneak around alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.74,0:10:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A contact lens case.\NI assume it's hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.83,0:10:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In which case,\Nthose glasses are the issue...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.33,0:10:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She probably forgot she\Nwas wearing contacts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.09,0:10:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's search the place! If this was\Na suicide, there might be a will!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.59,0:11:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.89,0:11:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with these pictures?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.14,0:11:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are photos she took\Non a recent company trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.27,0:11:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She liked drawing on\Npeople in their sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.15,0:11:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like they're\Nall the same pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.11,0:11:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's her signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.53,0:11:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The butterfly comes from\Nthe 'cho' in her name,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.20,0:11:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and she always puts it on her art.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.83,0:11:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her illustrations have\Ngotten popular lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.46,0:11:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No will in here either...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure. There was\Nnail polish on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.14,0:11:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that's the nail polish\Nthat went on sale today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.47,0:11:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone at school talked\Nabout its unique color.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.98,0:11:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, isn't that what's on this\Nsheet?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.94,0:11:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No question about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.07,0:12:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she didn't have any\Non her hands or feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.15,0:12:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only person wearing\Nthis color was...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.24,0:12:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.16,0:12:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.99,0:12:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It just happened to be\Npaint of the same color!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.54,0:12:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was working in my studio\Nuntil this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.67,0:12:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the killer.\NNo question about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.05,0:12:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he was in\Nthe office when she fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.80,0:12:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving now, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.18,0:12:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Just a little longer--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.02,0:12:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Disinfecting solution!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.81,0:12:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd. Judging from that case,\Nshe had soft lenses!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.65,0:12:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was only\Ndisinfectant in the fridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.82,0:12:44.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the saline solution?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.36,0:12:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure.\NWe haven't found a will.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.24,0:12:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it wasn't a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.87,0:12:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.58,0:12:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a courier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.96,0:12:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to leave a pick-up\Nreceipt when I came earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.96,0:13:00.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.25,0:13:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around 6:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.05,0:13:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,6:30?! That's when she jumped!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.22,0:13:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see her then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.93,0:13:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I was told I could pick\Nit up just inside the doorway
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and to come at exactly 6:30.\NI didn't actually meet anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.69,0:13:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's today's pick-up receipt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanaoka?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.15,0:13:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It says you were the one\Nwho requested the pick-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.16,0:13:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.83,0:13:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A courier at exactly the same time\Nshe dies-- seems fishy to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.96,0:13:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She told me over the phone\Nthat she finished a painting
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.42,0:13:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I simply arranged for a\Ncourier to deliver it to the editors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.34,0:13:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was tired and seemed odd,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.09,0:13:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I made it so she wouldn't\Nhave to wait on the courier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.60,0:13:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anything seem odd\Nwhen you entered the apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.06,0:13:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,\Nthe door slammed right open.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.07,0:14:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had barely even touched it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.94,0:14:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure she didn't do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.07,0:14:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so myself,\Nbut there was no one there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.28,0:14:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A nail fell, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.20,0:14:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A nail?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.83,0:14:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. And then I heard\Nsomething in the back break.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.79,0:14:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.67,0:14:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect! It's stuck on\Npart of the flowerpot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.31,0:14:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured it all out! With this trick,\Nit'd be possible to push her off
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.07,0:14:46.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the veranda from even miles away!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.78,0:14:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured out the killer's trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.33,0:14:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing?!\NI thought you left!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.25,0:15:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow! Stupid mosquitoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.55,0:15:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now I put this\NButton Speaker on the old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.01,0:15:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? You know who did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.51,0:15:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Chono-{\i1}san {\i0}didn't commit suicide.\NShe was murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.89,0:15:20.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By you, Hanaoka-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.44,0:15:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}. You know\Nhe couldn't have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.61,0:15:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! He couldn't be the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.11,0:15:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were all in that office\Nwhen we saw the lady fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.45,0:15:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.08,0:15:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet! He most certainly\Ncould have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.29,0:15:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He just needed strong\Nfishing line and a nail!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.00,0:15:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure. Can you get some?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.46,0:15:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.05,0:15:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a soy sauce bottle\Nand hot coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.68,0:15:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A soy sauce bottle and coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.56,0:16:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're heating the coffee at the moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.89,0:16:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but what are you trying to do here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.27,0:16:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please just humor me, if you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.19,0:16:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, make a loop\Nthat's long enough to go
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.57,0:16:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the veranda's railing\Nto the door and back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.33,0:16:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pull one end through the belt on\Nthe mattress, which'll be our victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.75,0:16:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then loop it around\Nthe railing, from the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.17,0:16:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then place that loop\Naround the flowerpot,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.63,0:16:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pull the line to the door while\Nkeeping the flowerpot from falling,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.47,0:16:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and temporarily place the\Nother loop around the intercom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.18,0:16:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, slide the victim along the\Nline and dangle her over the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.27,0:16:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, he covered\Nthe victim with the mattress.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.44,0:16:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It disguised the body,\Nlike camouflage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.45,0:16:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lastly, close the door\Non your way out,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.95,0:16:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,remove the loop around\Nthe intercom, and tie it to the nail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.28,0:17:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop the nail outside\Nthe door, and it's all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.79,0:17:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Once someone opens the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.63,0:17:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one end comes undone and\Nthe victim falls by herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.84,0:17:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The door opener was\NHanaoka-{\i1}san{\i0}'s courier, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.18,0:17:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He would open the door at\Nwhatever time he was asked to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.39,0:17:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting theory, but I don't\Nsee any fishing line at all--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.48,0:17:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.82,0:17:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.19,0:17:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With extra line and a soy sauce bottle,\Nit disappears like magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.78,0:17:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, you tie the extra line\Nbetween the victim and flowerpot,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.91,0:17:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pull the other end through\Nthe inner and outer drain caps,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.92,0:17:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and tie it to the soy sauce bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.34,0:17:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you simply place the\Nbottle and the caps into the drain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.51,0:18:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bottle is just a weight;\Nanything will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.64,0:18:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The saline solution missing\Nfrom the refrigerator, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.10,0:18:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing is believing...\NLet us open the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.53,0:18:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the door of fate that\Nwill solve this mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.29,0:18:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It went in!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.87,0:18:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Check the drain at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.25,0:18:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! We already found\Nfishing line and the saline solution!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.51,0:18:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous! I was on the phone\Nwith her just before she fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.09,0:18:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the one who called me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.60,0:18:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try redialing the office\Nwith the phone on the veranda!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.52,0:18:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It probably would connect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.89,0:18:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you used it to call the office\Nafter preparing the previous trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.32,0:18:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the voice that Tanaka-{\i1}san\N{\i0}heard was probably
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.91,0:19:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,part of the message on the\Nanswering machine in your studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.08,0:19:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On your way from here to the office,\Nyou stopped by your studio,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.92,0:19:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and took the tape\Nwith her voice on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.71,0:19:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the office, you went\Nstraight to the restroom
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.09,0:19:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and called the office\Nfrom your own cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.72,0:19:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Chono.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.35,0:19:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After taking the call from\NTanaka-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.06,0:19:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you diverted everyone's\Nattention to the opposite veranda
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.23,0:19:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it appear that the\Ndead woman committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.32,0:19:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder weapon was most\Nlikely the ashtray beneath the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.95,0:19:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you test it, it should\Nproduce a luminol reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.62,0:19:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, do you have any\Nproof that I killed her here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.59,0:20:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I certainly doubt it.\NAfter all, today is my first time here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.09,0:20:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Mori.\NHere's the hot coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.43,0:20:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.55,0:20:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take it to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.14,0:20:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, I'm innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.65,0:20:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.23,0:20:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.69,0:20:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that Chono-{\i1}san{\i0}'s signature?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.03,0:20:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. She drew it with\Nnail polish while he was asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.83,0:20:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how did you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.33,0:20:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was nail polish on the bed,\Nyet she had none on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.21,0:20:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while Hanaoka-{\i1}san\N{\i0}had some on his finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.51,0:20:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that nail polish\Nwent on sale today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.64,0:20:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're innocent,\Nthen answer this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.18,0:20:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When and where did you get\Nthat mark, and from whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.98,0:20:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't true, is it,\NHanaoka-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.86,0:21:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you\Nwould kill Chono-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.65,0:21:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His motive for murder was\Nprobably his paintings.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.99,0:21:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chono-{\i1}san{\i0}'s signature\Nappeared many times
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.04,0:21:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,beneath his own in his art album.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.04,0:21:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those were probably works\Nthat she made using his style.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.34,0:21:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That became a point of contention...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.59,0:21:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! It's exactly as you say!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.76,0:21:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I snapped, and when\NI came to, I had killed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.59,0:21:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that might not have\Nbeen the only reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.39,0:21:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was scared.\NScared of her young talent!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.48,0:21:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was a kind and beautiful girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.73,0:21:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost like the butterfly\Nthat flutters around flowers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.90,0:21:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she soon dominated those flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.99,0:21:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and started killing them by\Nsucking away too much nectar!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.95,0:21:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I plucked her wings so\Nshe could no longer fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.21,0:23:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? You want to use\NDad in a commercial?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.86,0:23:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll put him on right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.68,0:23:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the great\Ndetective Kogoro Mori!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.95,0:23:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad's really popular! An art\Nalbum and then a commercial!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.69,0:23:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it! He always gets the glory!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.32,0:23:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell, no! I'd never be\Nin such a commercial!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.24,0:23:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of commercial was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.03,0:23:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One for sleeping pills!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.18,0:23:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Said all I had to do\Nwas sleep! What nerve!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.24,0:23:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?\NThat's perfect for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.86,0:24:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that gasoline I smell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.99,0:24:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why the old man?\NDoes it have to do with the ghost ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.27,0:24:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No self-respecting detective\Nwould ever flee from danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.68,0:24:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.44,0:24:31.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ghost Ship Murder Case (Part 1)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.90,0:24:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.53,0:24:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ghost Ship Murder Case (Part 1).
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.96,0:24:49.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.38,0:24:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.47,0:24:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode is our first original multi-episode case.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.17,0:24:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you see the stars?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.43,0:24:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
